Esthange.\nWashington Gas Light common: 200 at 24 Peoples Drug Stores common 30 at 36%\nCotton Textile Dealings\nRemain Quiet in Week\nm\n1/ the Associated Press\nNEW YORK, May 21.\u2014There\nwas a flurry of buying in a few\nconstructions in the cotton textile\nmarket this week but the volume\nof sales remained small.\nBag manufacturers bought fair\nquantities of sheeting early in the\nweek. Some interest developed in\nbroadcloth and three-leaf twills.\nThe apparel trade took the twills\nfor lining and pocketing require\nments.\nThe price on popular 80-square\nprint cloth appeared generally\nestablished at 18\u00bb\u00a3 cents a yard.l\nWhere price firmness developed it\nreflected chiefly a tightening of\nsupplies as a result of more drastic i\nproduction curtailment by the\nmills.\nA great deal of attention was\nfocused on Goodyear Tire and\nRubber Company\u2019s announcement\nthat it will curtail operations 90\nper cent at its textile mils in Rock\nmart. Ga.\nOfficials of the company said\n(two things were behind the cut\nback\u2014reduced orders and high\nprices for cotton.\nWool goods lacked any fresh in\nfluenced. Fall goods orders to mills\nwere slow. Wool prices at the\nlatest Brisbane auctions rose each\nday of the week. The increasing\nprices in Australia dimmed hopes\nfor any very substantial decline\nin prices on 1950 spring lines.\n\nMaryland Tobacco\nAverage price* for moet grades offered\non the Southern Maryland tobacco auction\nmarkets displayed an Irregular trend yes\nterday. The United States Department\nof Agriculture and the Maryland State De\npartment of Markets reported the major\nity of fair heavy crop offerings brought\nslightly higher prices than on the day\nbefore, while fair tips were lower.\nAverage prices for thin crop and sec\nonds were relatively steady. Estimated\ndeliveries to the co-operative, under the\nGovernment loan program, ranged from\n5 to 20 per cent by markets.\nVolume of sales was fairly heavy In the\narea as a whole, although one market\ncompleted telling around noon. On Thurs\nday net sates amounted to 388.292 pounds\nfor 960.89 per hundred. Revised season\nauctions totaled 7.224,422 pounds for\n962.30.\nThe comparatively light sales for the\npast two days have relieved the conges\ntion in warehouses and packing plants to\nsoma extent. Conditions are expected to\nbe even better when marketing is re\n*U Average'auctioB bid prices pert hundred\npounds on a limited number of repre\nsentative u. 8. grade /rlday. follow:\nHeavy crop\u2014Oood cherry-red. BSP,\n984; fair eherry-redTB4F. $58; fair green\nish. B4V. 939; fair red, B4R, 340\nTips\u2014Pair eherry-red. T4F, 942; fair\nred, T4R. 924; fair green. T4G.il 4.50\nThin crop\u2014Fine cherry-red. C2F, 968;\ngood cherry-red, C3F. $67: fair cneiTy\nredT C4F. $86: fair red, C4R. $81; low\ncherry-red, C6F. $59._\nNO MONEY\nSHORTAGE\nWe Have Plenty!\nBut w\u00ab are alwayt thort\nof good Firet Trutt Loant.\nWhat it yeur proportion?\nOmr home-financing tpe\neialiitt want to work for\nyou\u2014help you kuy your\nhome or refinance your\npreient mortgage. Come\nin\u2014let\u2019i talk it overt\nnOwestern\n/ScC&fal/,\nSAVINGS ft LOAOSSN.\ni\n1337 G Straat N.W.\nRE. 5262\nBranchs Takoma Park\nINSURED\nSAVINGS PLUS\nSUBSTANTIAL\nDIVIDENDS\nBoth Are Your* at\nHOME MUTUAL\nBUILDING A LOAN ASSOCIATION\n93! 15th St. N.W. NATIONAL 4131\nMember: Federal Savings 9 Loan Insurance Carp.\nCLARENCE E. KEFAUVER, JR.\nCERTIFIED PUBLIC ACCOUNTANT\nMemberi American Institute af AccountantI\nANNOUNCES\nTHE OPENING OF AN OFFICE\nFOR THE GENERAL PRACTICE\nof\nPUBLIC ACCOUNTING\nt\nincluding\nAudits, Systems and Taxes\nCOLUMBIA PBOIRAL BUILDlN*\n710 Ktovwrtli **Mt N.W. STarltnf 2015\nProduce Markets\nBaltimore quotation* furnished br the\nunited State* Department of Agriculture\nApplea\u2014Market about steady bu*hel\nbasket*. U. S No. 1. Virginia Wlnessp*.\nInches up 3.00: few. 3 25; Yorks,\nboxes 180s 3 75.\nPotatoes-New market slightly weaker\non North Carolin